The paper proposes an automated latent fingerprint recognition algorithm that utilizes Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNets) for ridge flow estimation and minutiae descriptor extraction, and extract complementary templates (two minutiae templates and one texture template) to represent the latent. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with forensic agencies and law enforcement, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of ConvNets also suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval and database search, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
